Since I live in Japan I am forced to use it, but Line is the exact example of how a messaging app doesn't have to be. A behemoth app, slow, battery hungry, and with tons of feature unnecessary. Messages come late. Notifications come late. Calls and video calls work, but they consume battery like crazy. Social features are completely useless and they can't be disabled. Chats have to be deleted one by one. Multiple selection isn't possible. What else? Terrible.

Backup process has only gotten worse over time. In the past, at least you could save all your data, if in a manual and tedious process. Instead of improving this by a simple loop all function, Line has moved to Google Drive that only saves the text. No images are saved. And this process is very buggy and fails often. Line is too cheap to have their servers handle backups, too lazy to code a simple loop all for the old method and now too shortsighted to make Google Drive work well.

Be warned! I Lost about 10 years of chat history in an instant after upgrading my phone. My precious conversations, photos, and videos, gone. When you log in on a new device, like after getting a new phone, your entire history is erased on the old device. Unless you first explored deep in the settings menu to manually link a Google drive account and backup the chat, you lose everything. It would have been great to get a warning like "By logging in will lose chat history on other devices, click here to learn how to backup," or better yet, if it would just backup automatically without the user needed to dig into the settings. It's 2020, this shouldn't have happened. Worse thing is, the app on my old phone is still consuming ~0.9GB of storage, so I KNOW my chats and photos are still there, but no longer accessible. I am appalled. I have never reviewed an app in my 10+ years of using Android (bad on me, maybe) But this has motivated me to warn others and to beg the developers to fix this. I'm sure I'm not the only one, either.
